definition: no use to tell others/let's keep this between ourselves (idiom)
pinyin: bu4 zu2 wei2 wai4 ren2 dao4

definition: to give no cause for anxiety/nothing to worry about
to fall short of the best but be better than the worst/can pass muster
pinyin: bi3 shang4 bu4 zu2 bi3 xia4 you3 yu2

definition: avaricious and insatiable (idiom); greedy and never satisfied
not to be taken as an example/not an example to be followed/not to be taken as authoritative

sentences.english: Some 28 percent of adolescents say they are too tired to exercise, due to sleep.
sentences.chinese: 28%的年轻人表示，由于睡眠不足而没劲儿运动。

sentences.english: Moreover, the relatively high proportion of mature or over-mature forests shows that resources in support are insufficient.
sentences.chinese: 近成过熟林所占比例较大，后备资源不足。

sentences.english: Not enough cooling power could mean heatstroke or dehydration.
sentences.chinese: 冷却能力不足会造成中暑脱水。

sentences.english: The downside is that you won't get a formal diagnosis nor prescription.
sentences.chinese: 不足之处是你无法得到正式的诊断书及处方。

sentences.english: As the lack of understanding of the disease, it's often misdiagnosed or missed diagnosis.
sentences.chinese: 由于对该疾病认识的不足，经常被误诊或者漏诊。

sentences.english: Ru handed down less than one hundred works, so very precious.
sentences.chinese: 汝窑传世作品不足百件，因此非常珍贵。

sentences.english: Most of the time this is due to insufficient memory.
sentences.chinese: 大多数时候，这是由于内存不足。

sentences.english: One is lack of recognition of the seriousness of the problem.
sentences.chinese: 一个是对这个问题的严重性认识不足。

sentences.english: The centre reserves the right to cancel a programme if there is insufficient number of enrollments.
sentences.chinese: 如报读人数不足，本中心有权取消有关课程。

sentences.english: Pure cotton grey fabric prices fell modestly, trading volume is still insufficient.
sentences.chinese: 纯棉坯布价格小幅下滑，成交量仍显不足。

sentences.english: One day is hardly enough to show our gratitude。
sentences.chinese: 仅这一天远不足以表达我们对您的感激之情。

sentences.english: Flowrate insufficient or too low head.
The most insignificant transgression reverberated in the most ethereal worlds.
sentences.chinese: 最微不足道的罪行在最超越尘俗的天地里引起回响。

sentences.english: Pairs of Private Vocational Colleges dissatisfied with lack of self-affirmation, strong inferiority complex.
sentences.chinese: 对民办高职院校感到不满，自我肯定不足，自卑感强。

sentences.english: Germany, like Japan, is bedevilled by chronically weak domestic demand.
sentences.chinese: 德国和日本一样，被长期的国内需求不足而困扰。

sentences.english: It's no surprise that computer repair companies are thriving.
sentences.chinese: 电脑修理业繁荣起来就不足为怪了。

definition: to be on the low side/to be inadequate (e.g. of a salary)
range (the difference between the lowest and highest values)
to be deficient in sth/to be short of sth (supplies, money etc)
short stave of the barrel (which allows the contents to escape)/(fig.) shortcoming/weak point
to bring up to full strength/to make up a deficiency/to fill (a vacancy, gap etc)
